reflection: Dr. Smith introduced me to a new breathing technique that really helped during our session. We talked about identifying triggers at work and how to respond differently. I feel more equipped to handle stressful situations now. Planning to practice the 4-7-8 breathing method daily.

Had a breakthrough moment discussing my relationship with my parents. Realized I've been taking on too much responsibility for their emotions. Dr. Smith helped me understand that setting boundaries isn't selfish - it's necessary for my mental health. Going to try having a conversation with them this week.

Started the year with a focus on being kinder to myself. We discussed how my inner critic has been particularly harsh lately. Created a list of realistic goals rather than overwhelming resolutions. The concept of 'good enough' really resonated with me today.

Christmas was challenging but I used the mindfulness techniques we've been practicing. When things got overwhelming at dinner, I excused myself for a few minutes of deep breathing. It made such a difference in how I handled the rest of the evening.
